articles.author: Gaea Katreena Cabico
articles.title: Two cases of Omicron BN.1 subvariant detected in Philippines - Philstar.com
articles.description: BN.1 is a sublineage of Omicron BA.2.75 subvariant. It is considered a “variant under monitoring” by the European Center for Disease Control due to its increasing prevalence globally.
articles.content:
MANILA, Philippines — Two cases of BN.1, a descendant of the Omicron variant, have been detected in the Philippines, the Department of Health said Friday.
